item.title: [+1666] uTorrent 2.0 To Elimininate The Need For ISP Throttling
item.description: BitTorrent Inc. is about to launch a completely improved implementation of the BitTorrent protocol that will benefit both users and ISPs. uTorrent 2.0, which is currently being tested by thousands of people, will eliminate the need for ISPs to throttle or stop BitTorrent traffic, and will optimize the download experience for its users.

item.title: [+1361] Man sues after Axe body spray fails to land him a girlfriend
item.description: A luckless Indian romeo is suing Lynx after he failed to land a single girlfriend during seven years of using their products. Vaibhav Bedi, 26, is seeking £26,000 from parent company Unilever for the "depression and psychological damage" caused by the lack of any Lynx effect.

item.title: [+504] Six Drugs Scientists May Resign Over Nutt Sacking
item.description: Leading members of the Advisory Council on the Misuse of Drugs (ACMD) are expected to resign over the sacking of its chairman, leaving the service in disarray, one of its leading scientists has warned. Six of its scientists will resign from the independent organisation, putting further pressure on the Government over its handling of the affair.
